lieved to be reliable and uptodate however their accuracy and completeness cannot be guaranteed opinions expressed reflect judgment current as of the date of this publication and are subject to change opinions expressed are current as of the date of the materials and are subject to change the materials on this site should in no way be construed as investment advice nor a solicitation to buy or sell securities or insurance products and services no investment actions should be implemented based on the materials presented herein   investment risk investment involves risk the value of an investment as well as income associated with investments is not guaranteed and may fluctuate accordingly investments may decline below what was originally invested   international investing international investing especially in emerging markets involves special risks such as currency exchange political and economic risks  alternative investments alternative investments involve a higher degree of risk because they may engage in leveraging or other speculative investment practices that may increase the risk of investment loss alternative investments can also be highly illiquid   reits reits may be subject to greater volatility than investments in traditional securities and pose special risks the value of real estate and portfolios that invest in real estate may fluctuate due to losses from causality or condemnation changes in local and general economic conditions supply and demand interest rates property taxes and regulatory limitations on rents zoning laws and operating expenses   commodities commodities may be subject to greater volatility than securities and pose special risks investments in commodities may be affected by changes in interest rates and other factors such as weather disease embargoes and international economic and political developments   high yield bonds high yield bonds are lower grade bonds whose principal may be subject to greater fluctuation than investments in higher rated bonds use of these instruments may involve certain costs and risks such as liquidity risk interest rate risk and credit risk   indices index performance is shown as total return you cannot invest directly in an index but you can invest in securities that track an index index funds are weighted and so may not perform in unison with the index   professional designations cfp certified financial planner board of standards inc owns the certification marks cfp® certified financial planner™ and federally registered cfp with flame design in the us which it awards to individuals who successfully complete cfp boards initial and ongoing certification requirements cfa chartered financial analyst cfa charter is a professional designation established in  and awarded by the cfa institute to earn the cfa charter candidates must pass three sequential sixhour examinations over two to four years the three levels of the cfa program test a wide range of investment topics including ethical and professional standards fixedincome analysis alternative and derivative investments and portfolio management and wealth planning in addition cfa charterholders must have at least four years of acceptable professional experience in the investment decisionmaking process and must commit to abide by and annually reaffirm their adherence to the cfa institute code of ethics and standards of professional conduct httpwwwcfainstituteorgaboutuspoliciescfaguidehtml   adv disclosure to receive a copy of the ctc mycfo llc investment advisory disclosure form adv parts a or b please contact the firm directly at     website terms of use please read these website terms of use carefully by accessing this website including the websites of bmo harris bank na and its affiliates operating in the united states which collectively are referred to as bmo harris with all such websites collectively being referred to as this website you agree to be bound by these website terms of use bmo harris may amend these website 