al warming and sealevel rise by reducing super climate pollutants called hydrofluorocarbons or hfcs cutting hfcs will avoid half a degree of global warming by the end of the century this would be a big contribution to the historic  paris agreement find out more about reducing hfcs and why it matters with this video which is narrated by durwood zaelke of the institute of governance and sustainable development watch our explainer video about hfcs beatties story how often do we stop and try to see the world from a childs perspective for many it can be a complex and dangerous place join beattie on a journey through her early years check out our interactive childrens story endowment over the past decade ciffs endowment has grown to a value of nearly  billion after charitable activities and costs with this strong financial base we have built a growing portfolio of charitable grants with a value of over threequarters of a billion dollars in the  financial year grant disbursements rose to  million read more  twitter x back the childrens investment fund management  wikipedia the childrens investment fund management from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search the children’s investment fund management uk llp tci is a london‐based hedge fund management firm founded by chris hohn in  which manages the children’s investment master fund tci makes long‐term investments in companies globally the management company is authorized and regulated in the united kingdom by the financial services authority like most hedge funds tci requires investors to commit their capital for multiyear periods this longterm horizon allows the fund greater flexibility when trading and investing capital independent of any potential ad hoc time constraints contents  charity  investor activism  awards  references  external links  articles charityedit main article the childrens investment fund foundation tci derives its name from a charitable foundation called the childrens investment fund foundation ciff set up by chris hohn and his exwife jamie cooperhohn in an example of venture philanthropy ciff initially received a portion of tci’s profits and other donations ciff focuses on improving the lives of children living in poverty in developing countries and has grown to be one of the largest charities in the united kingdom after suffering a  loss during the  calendar year as of july  the previous financial year had seen a rebound of over  profit and revenue for tci through changes set in motion in  the fund and foundation were split up the fund no longer donates money to the foundation on a contractual basis though it may do on a discretionary basis investor activismedit tci has a reputation for aggressive shareholder activism some criticswho believe that it has taken an active role in most situations to promote its own agenda under the guise of sound corporate governance and increase shareholder value tci has been a major shareholder of the german stock exchange deutsche börse where it forced the resignation of the ceo after he refused to abandon his plan to take over the london stock exchange in  after acquiring  of the shares of major dutch bank abn amro tci led an attack demanding the bank split up or sell to the highest bidder to produce shareholder value abn was ultimately split and sold to royal bank of scotland rbs fortis and banco santander and was a major contributing factor in the downfall of both rbs and fortis in june  tci failed in its attempt to get the japanese utility jpower in which it had acquired a  stake to boost its dividend the general meeting of shareholders rejected the proposal prompting a severe selloff in the stock in  as a shareholder of both mittal steel company and arcelor tci supported mittal steel in the companys unsolicited takeover offer for arcelor however when mittal steel subsequently attempted to acquire arcelor brasil one of arcelors subsidiaries without an appropriate premium tci defended the rights of arcelor brasil’s minority shareholders causing mittal to raise its offer price more than citation needed tci initiated legal action against the government of india using provisions in the bilateral trade treaty between united kingdom and india regarding the under pricing of coal by coal india limitedin which tci holds  stake in  the company was suffering from heavy losses but recovered very well and assets under management reportedly stood around  billion earlier this year and at the end of  the company recorded a loss of  in profits as a result of reduced investment performance awardsedit the fund won eurohedge’s european hedge fund of the year award in    referencesedit  opalesque  july  tci sees big rebound in    tci hedge fund in britain ends ties to charitable arm  june    businessweek—a little fund with big demands  nrc handelsblad dutch newspaper february    bs reporter  march  tci starts legal action against indian govt under uk cyprus treaties   tci sees profits fall  efinancialnewscom retrieved  september    childrens investment fund profile  tci jabre toscafund vr lead eurohedge awards  winners external linksedit tci website articlesedit this articles use of external links may not follow wikipedias policies or guidelines please improve this article by removing excessive or inappropriate external links and converting useful links where appropriate into footnote references july  learn how and when to remove this template message financial times feared fund turns to business of charity by james mackintosh july   management today the new new philanthropists by ian wylie october   spectator the real driving force in the battle for abn by matthew lynn may   financial news financial news   the economist leader of the swarm july   the independent financier in record £m donation to charity by arifa akbar july   wainewright will whats in a name the childrens investment fund management password access hfm week  september  hedge fund dumps stake in csx new york times dealbook 